tip.text: A great hotel. It used to be a mining company, but now it's a boutique hotel. With Maasmechelen Outlet & a movie theater around the corner. Breakfast is nice, but overpriced. Service is excellent
The restaurant is owned by young entrepeneurs Pascal and Toby. It's a feel good place where you can have a good glass of champagne for €6,50. Must try starters: artichoke or burrata. We'll be back!

This is by far the best yakatori restaurant in Amsterdam. They serve cold sake you can only find in Japan. Great staff, and not too expensive. A true Japanese gem, where Japanese people eat frequently
If interior design is more important than food, then this the place to be. The food is not bad, but they overcharge you. For the best Chinese food, check out Hoi Tin on the Zeedijk (city centre).
A nice styled but still cozy winebar, where they also serve champagne by the glass. Don't forget to taste their variety on bites.
Must try: Fiorentina. This place is wonderful: you choose your meat as if you're at the butcher. Then you're seated at a table. Never tasted such good Fiorentina. Friendly staff, and nicely priced

At the back entrance of the Amsterdam central station (IJzijde). Seafood that is prepared with love for food. But also great because both the manager and the chef are passionate about their profession
You don't have to travel to Asia for the best pho in town. At Pho 91 they serve the real deal. I can recommend the Pho 91, with thin beef and chicken slices. Their broth is exceptionally flavoured.

formattedAddress: Pavilion Kuala Lumpur (Lot C4.07.00, Connection Level 4)

tip.text: Choose the special with pork belly and a soft boiled egg. This variety can be chosen with several sorts of ramen.

formattedAddress: Pavilion Kuala Lumpur (Lot C4.07.00, Connection Level 4)

tip.text: A superb hotel: service and staff are top notch. Make sure you book a room in the "old building", with access to the club lounge. For a luxurious stay in KL, the Majestic is a must-stay!
Although the food was okay, and the staff friendly we thought it was too noisy. Also the smoke coming from the grill was all over the place. It's great though that it's located in Amsterdam Oost
Authentic Dutch food like 'draadjesvlees' (beef stew) or 'stamppot met worst'. Chef Peter van der Linden makes his rounds to chat with customers. Very good value for money & great staff. #mustgo
On Saturdays they serve Japanese fingerfood until 02.30 hrs. On every other day, the kitchen is open until half an hour before closing time. They are closed on Monday. Every dish is worth tasting
Great food, several extraordinary dishes. Meat dishes from the grill have a special flavour. Good staff and interior design.
The bar keeper makes killer cocktails, and contrary to most bars: you get most of the cocktails in long drink glasses. Very good value for money 😁
Great food and interior, unfortunately rather noisy.
Gr8 theming.❤️ the pinball machine,snack drawers with t-shirts&hot sauces.Staff is friendly,but: the drinks menu came when I already ordered 2 drinks out of the blind 😔 Food is ok but luke warm
Really tasteful yakitori and udon. Very friendly staff. A must go if you enjoy the Japanese kitchen. Try the 2 sake on the photo. Top one is dry, bottom one has more flavour.
Wow, so happy we stumbled upon this place. Great staff, and their starters are superb! Try the firecrackers and Thai beggar's pouch. You won't regret it!
Love the make your own egg & cheese combo. But their espresso is awful, seriously!
P.S. great ambiance as well. That is, if you like industrial.
Here the chefs really know how to prepare red meat. And the staff is more than friendly. Check my photo, and get hungry! Making reservations is advisable 😉
Definitely a must-go. Besides the very friendly staff, the pasta's are beyond gr8. Try the truly spicy arrabiata with additional ricotta. And the ani-pasto Cantinetta is de-li-cious! Nice wine too!
The food, and of course the location. Try the cheese fondue, it is served in a round bun and is delicious. For starters, I can recomend the anti-pasta.
Bruschetta and steak mackerel
Steak tartare, bavette, steak mackerel. In fact, everything on the menu is great. As dessert try the cheese! Oh and by the way, love their toilet. It feels very James Bond..
This is a hidden gem in Amsterdam. Not easy to find, but worth the search. The chef uses only biological ingredients, and is a true kitchen wizard. Try the artichoke (starter) or the steak tartare.
